Senate Resolution 116
By: Senators Goodman of the 8th, Watson of the 11th, Summers of the 13th and Hickman
of the 4th
A RESOLUTION
1 Congratulating the Lanier County High School baseball team for winning the GHSA Class
2 A Division II State Baseball Championship; and for other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, the Lanier County High School baseball team has established and maintained
4 a proud tradition of excellence with equal emphases on character and academics; and
5 WHEREAS, excellent play, superior teamwork, and extraordinary leadership made this team
6 a spectacular one to observe throughout the season, and as a fitting finale to its extraordinary
7 2024 campaign, the team triumphed in a hard-fought battle to become the GHSA Class A
8 Division II State Baseball Champions; and
9 WHEREAS, the phenomenal performance of the team is a clear indication of the outstanding
10 athletic ability, dedication, hard work, and unity of purpose and spirit of each member of the
11 team; its superb batting and fielding talents; and the astute direction of head coach John
12 White; and
13 WHEREAS, Grant Gano, the team's MVP, excelled in play by hitting a grand slam in
14 overtime, supported by his team who performed with precision throughout the season and
